[{"id":"VR855014","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram consisting of, from left to right along a horizontal line, an object, a convex mirror, and an image. The object points upward, and the distance between it and the mirror is D sub 0. The image points upward, is shorter than the object, and the distance between it and the mirror is D sub i on the right side of the convex mirror. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR855014.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An object is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub o\"><math alttext=\"D sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> in front of a convex mirror, as shown in the figure. The image formed by the mirror is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub i\"><math alttext=\"D sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> behind the mirror, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub i, is less than D sub o\"><math alttext=\"D sub i, is less than D sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Where is the focal point of the mirror located relative to the mirror?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR855014_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator D sub o, end sub, times D sub i, and denominator D sub o, end sub, plus D sub i, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator D sub o, end sub, times D sub i, and de